TTEERRMM -- Environmental Variable

Name the default terminal type
TTEERRMM=_t_e_r_m_i_n_a_l _t_y_p_e

The environmental  variable TTEERRMM  names the type  of terminal that  you are
using.  This  variable is read  by every program  that uses the  tteerrmmccaapp or
tteerrmmiinnffoo library,  to ensure that the correct  terminal description is read
when the program is invoked.  You should set this variable in your pprrooffiillee,
to ensure that  the system understands what type of  terminal you use.  The
file /eettcc/pprrooffiillee sets TTEERRMM to aannssiippcc.

_S_e_e _A_l_s_o
eennvviirroonnmmeennttaall vvaarriiaabblleess, mmee, tteerrmmccaapp
